: 정남향으로 하루 종일 해가 잘 들어 밝고 환합니다.
  넓은 잔디 마당과 예쁜 정원을 바라보실 수 있어요.

[안채] 첫 번째 침실 (퀸사이즈, 나비드 라텍스) 
: 최대 2인까지만 주무실 수 있어요.
  Master Bedroom으로 가장 큰 침실입니다.
  (바닥에서 주무실 공간은 없습니다)

[안채] 두 번째 침실 (퀸사이즈, 시몬스 뷰티레스트)
: 침대방이며, 최대 2인까지만 주무실 수 있어요.
  첫 번째 침실 보다 방 크기가 작습니다. 
  (침대 높이가 어느 정도 있습니다)
  (바닥에서 주무실 공간은 없습니다)

[안채] 욕조욕실 (소프트욕조)
: 첫 번째 침실에 연결되어 있습니다. 
  정남향으로 밝은 햇살 속에서 입욕 하실 수 있어요. 
  딱딱하지 않은 말랑한 특수 재질의 소프트욕조입니다. 
  거품입욕제 제공합니다.

[안채] 드레스룸/파우더룸
: 첫 번째 침실에 연결되어 있어요.
  좌측이 화장대, 우측이 붙박이장입니다.

[안채] 공용욕실 (변기, 세면대, 샤워실)
: 거실에 연결되어 있습니다.
  바닥까지 난방이 되므로 겨울에 춥지 않아요.
  건식 욕실 구조로 편히 이용 가능합니다.

[바깥채(다이닝카페)] 
: 카페 스타일로 꾸며져 있습니다. 
  타숙소와는 달리 음식 조리에 제한을 두지 않습니다.

[바깥채(다이닝카페)]
: 3구 전기렌지, 세탁기, 냉장고(냉동고), 전기포트, 네스프레소, 토스트기, 전기밥솥, 전자렌지 등이 있어요. 각종 식기와 기본양념류가 구비되어 있으며, 특히! 냉장고의 경우 사이즈가 넉넉해 편리합니다.

[바깥채(다이닝카페)]
: 다양한 도서, 야마하오디오, 보드게임이 있어요.
  책은 300권 이상이며, 보드게임도 종류가 많습니다.
  안락 의자가 있어 편히 책과 음악을 즐기실 수 있어요.

[바깥채(다이닝카페)] 
: 식탁에서 바라본 비오는 날의 정원 모습입니다. 
  맑은 날도 좋지만 비오는 날에는 더욱더 운치 있는 제주를 느낄 수 있어요.

[바깥채(다이닝카페)]
 : 다이닝 테이블에 앉아 예쁜 정원을 바라보며
   감미로운 음악과 함께 여유로운 시간을 보내보세요.
   300여 권의 책들 중에서 마음에 드는 책 한 권을 골라 읽어보시는 것도 좋겠죠?

[바깥채(다이닝카페)]
: 창 밖으로 길게 심어진 로즈마리를 보실 수 있어요. 
  로즈마리 꽃이 필 때는 보라색 꽃이 너무 예쁘고요. 
  동백이 피는 계절에는 붉게 핀 동백꽃들도 즐기 실 수 있어요. 
  올 해는 수국을 길게 심어볼까 합니다.

[바깥채(다이닝카페)] 야마하 오디오
: 블루투스, 라디오, CD, USB 등 다양한 매체로 음악을 즐기실 수 있어요. 
  특별히, 준비한 음악이 없다면 주인장이 시즌별로 선곡한 음악을 들으셔도 됩니다.

[바깥채 (다이닝카페)] 테라스
: 바깥채에 연결된 테라스입니다.

Plenty of space for cooking- cooking basics provided
Don't judge me for doing a terrible job making these beds! The top bunk is hard!
The dining table converts to a sleeping space. It's 5 feet long, so not for adults, but it's not bad for extra TV watching space
Sleeping space for adults, a nice queen bed. This room has a door for privacy which is rare in a camper. Escape the kids!
You might meet children on their walk home from Monyo village's pre-school nursery if you camp here (see left hand-side)
...be warned though, they may invite others
But we're getting ahead of ourselves: First you must travel to Nyachikadza Island by canoe from Kome Port on the mainland.
At Kome Port, you will meet Bonface Chamambala, a representative of the chief of the village where you will camp.  Bonface will escort you the rest of the way.
Bonface is a teacher and coordinator at Monyo Village pre-school nursery and youth club.
...everything travels to and from Nyachikadza Island by canoe.
The canoe trip takes about 40 minutes. Enjoy it :)
Once you arrive at Nyachikadza Port...
...expect plenty of curious help loading your bags onto the motorbikes.
The motorbike trip to Monyo Village, where you'll camp, takes about 20 minutes...
Chief Monyo, at whose pleasure you are warmly welcomed for the duration of your stay in his group of villages.
Dinner of nsima, beans and fish will be served once you've pitched your tent and have settled.
After dinner, if you're really lucky it might be 'Nyachikadza Cinema Night', which usually attracts a couple of hundred people
In fact as cinema-night tends to create quite a bit of excitement, with queues forming hours before the screening, you'll already know if it's on or not that night.
...but for an extra $20, we can guarantee you it'll be on! ;)
...and David Attenborough works in every language

Antonini's Village complex is located on the northwest side of the island, close to the New Port  and Mykonos Town.
It takes only 17 minutes to get off the airport.  The distance is 7,6 Km. If you need a  taxi/ bus transfer with extra cost  or a rental car, a scooter or ATV  do not hesitate to contact us!
Antonini's Village is 3.4 km away from the New Port, to which all ferries and large sea jets arrive. Some sea jets arrive at the Old Port.

Αntonini's Village complex is 4.5 km from Mykonos Town and the Old Port, from which some sea jets arrive. All ferries  and large sea jets arrive at New Port of Tourlos, 2 km from Antoninis village. The pier for boats  to Delos is in Chora, the city center which is a walking area as  vehicles are not allowed inside Mykonos town. The public parking is at the Old Port, 500 m away from Mykonos Town.

The "Armenistis Lighthouse" is just 1.2 km from the Antonini's Village Complex. You can also walk on foot to the uphill road.  The area around Armenistis Lighthouse is a "Natural Landscape Conservation Area". It is worth a visit.
The area where Antonini's Village is located is called "Houlakia".  Houlakia is an area of immense beauty and a "Natural Monument of Particular Importance".
In the  Mykonian dialect, "Houlakia" means pebble, stone that has become round by the wave.
"Houlakia" is a beach where there isn’t sand but big and colorful pebbles. This area is protected and it is forbidden to take away of these round pebbles. We suggest you to take a visit there.
A ferry arrives at the New Port of Mykonos .. Are you in the ferry?  :) Houlakia beach.
Agios Stefanos is the closet sandy beach, 1.5 klm far from Antonini’s Village. There you can find restaurants, bars, ATM, Mini Market, rental car/scooter office, and the public bus station.
Agios Stefanos  is one of the most popular beaches in Mykonos, as it is the closest beach from Mykonos Town (Chora), next to the Νew Port of Mykonos.

View of the canal.  This area is open to all guests to enjoy fishing or just hanging by the water.  Across the canal you will see many birds and we currently have an Eagle's nest.  There are other units available- Fish Room, Wheel Room and Park Model

This is a shared large char pit area open for all guests to use.  We just ask that you do not leave an active fire unattended.
